<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFDFFBCFF3D9A496BD47B86" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9A4968657B24" blockId="16.[151,756,1549,1767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF3D9A4968057B44" bold="true" box="[151,264,1549,1573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Remarks:</emphasis>
It resembles the specimens recorded by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9A096BD47B86" blockId="16.[151,756,1549,1767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF3D9A0968C47B04" bold="true" box="[151,457,1613,1637]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally described from the Paleocene (Dano-Montian) of 
<collectingCountry id="32CB7663FFFDFFBCFD949A2A6B9C7BE7" box="[574,657,1646,1670]" name="Algeria" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, and also recorded from the Danian in northern Sinai by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956). In the study area, it is found in the Maastrichtian and Early-Middle Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
